node.text: We looked at three kinds of salt under a high-powered microscope and found that grains of table salt are tiny cubes, grains of Morton Kosher Salt are hard and dense, and grains of Diamond Crystal Kosher Salt are hollow and delicate. That's why the measurements of table salt and kosher salts differ. Tap the link in our bio to learn more about our taste test of kosher salt.
